<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF83F210FF3BF865D1A7F84C" bold="true" box="[136,249,1992,2014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="118">FIGURE 3</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="DBD94D60FF83F210FEB5F865D0A8F84C" authorityName="Z. L. Liang &amp; Li Bing Zhang" authorityYear="2021" box="[262,502,1992,2013]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Polystichum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="menglaense">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF83F210FEB5F865D0A8F84C" box="[262,502,1992,2013]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="118">Polystichum menglaense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.—A. Habitat.—B. Portion of abaxial lamina from a dry specimen.—C. Habit of the plant on the rock in the shade.—D. Basal petiole scale.—E. Microscale from abaxial lamina surface.—F. Rachis scale.—G. Portion of abaxial lamina from a freshly collected specimen.
</paragraph>
