<paragraph id="1C6636E3FF82F211FF0EFE83D3B2FEFC" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,869]" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FF0EFE83D0A8FED9" bold="true" box="[189,502,302,328]" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Geographical distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="DBD94D60FF82F211FDAAFE83D26EFED9" authorityName="Z. L. Liang &amp; Li Bing Zhang" authorityYear="2021" box="[537,816,302,328]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Polystichum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="menglaense">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FDAAFE83D26EFED9" box="[537,816,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Polystichum menglaense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<materialsCitation id="ACB13CBEFF82F211FC8BFE83D428FED9" box="[824,1398,302,329]" county="Mengla County" location="Mengla County" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Yunnan">
is only found in 
<collectingCounty id="F5074E6FFF82F211FC46FE83D5F9FED9" box="[1013,1191,302,328]" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Mengla County</collectingCounty>
, 
<collectingRegion id="DE1DF801FF82F211FB01FE82D428FED9" box="[1202,1398,302,329]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Yunnan Province</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
, and may represent an endemic species to southern 
<collectingRegion id="DE1DF801FF82F211FD3CFEFED3B6FEFC" box="[655,744,339,365]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="54C36568FF82F211FF0EFEDBD473FDB1" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="1C6636E3FF82F211FF0EFEDBD0F9FE24" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,869]" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FF0EFEDBD042FE01" bold="true" box="[189,284,374,400]" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Ecology</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="DBD94D60FF82F211FEF3FEDBD306FE01" authorityName="Z. L. Liang &amp; Li Bing Zhang" authorityYear="2021" box="[320,600,374,400]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Polystichum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="menglaense">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FEF3FEDBD306FE01" box="[320,600,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Polystichum menglaense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was observed to grow on limestone rocks under tropical rain forest, at an elevation of about 
<specimenCount id="0ADFFD6AFF82F211FEEAFE37D0F9FE24" box="[345,423,410,437]" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" type="generic">
<quantity id="DB219B06FF82F211FEEAFE37D0FDFE24" box="[345,419,410,437]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" unit="m" value="700.0">700 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1C6636E3FF82F211FF0EFE13D473FDB1" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,869]" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FF0EFE13D0B1FE49" bold="true" box="[189,495,446,472]" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">IUCN Red List category</emphasis>
:—Only one population of 
<taxonomicName id="DBD94D60FF82F211FC82FE13D512FE49" authorityName="Z. L. Liang &amp; Li Bing Zhang" authorityYear="2021" box="[817,1100,446,472]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Polystichum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="menglaense">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FC82FE13D512FE49" box="[817,1100,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Polystichum menglaense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in Mengla. Based on current information and following the IUCN (The International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources) guidelines (
<bibRefCitation id="78484B12FF82F211FE3EFDABD343FDB1" author="IUCN" box="[397,541,518,544]" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" refId="ref3082" refString="IUCN. (2017) The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2017 - 1. Available at: www. iucnredlist. org." type="book" year="2017">IUCN, 2017</bibRefCitation>
), this new species should be classified as Critically Endangered (CR).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="54C36568FF82F211FF0EFD87D53BFCF4" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="1C6636E3FF82F211FF0EFD87D533FD1C" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,869]" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FF0EFD87D060FDD5" bold="true" box="[189,318,554,580]" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The species epithet is based on the Chinese pinyin, 
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FC1BFD87D2A4FDD5" box="[936,1018,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">mengla</emphasis>
, the county name in southern 
<collectingRegion id="DE1DF801FF82F211FAFCFD86D4F6FDD4" box="[1359,1448,555,581]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, and the Latin suffix 
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FEDFFDE2D0F6FDF9" box="[364,424,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">-ense</emphasis>
, of origin, referring to the 
<typeStatus id="C3628841FF82F211FD65FDE2D258FDF8" box="[726,774,591,617]" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">type</typeStatus>
locality and the current known distribution of the species in Mengla County, 
<collectingRegion id="DE1DF801FF82F211FEF1FDDED0C5FD1C" box="[322,411,627,653]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
. The Chinese name is suggested as ‘©腊耳蕨 (meng la er jue)’.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1C6636E3FF82F211FF0EFD3BD53BFCF4" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,869]" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FF0EFD3BD05EFD21" bold="true" box="[189,256,662,688]" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Notes</emphasis>
:—In Mengla, the southernmost part of 
<collectingRegion id="DE1DF801FF82F211FD08FD3AD24AFD20" box="[699,788,663,689]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, there are only three species belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="DBD94D60FF82F211FB5BFD3BD00BFD45" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Polystichum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Haplopolystichum">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FB5BFD3BD42CFD21" box="[1256,1394,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Polystichum</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FF3BFD17D00BFD45" box="[136,341,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Haplopolystichum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FED5FD16D0ABFD45" box="[358,501,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">
<taxonomicName id="DBD94D60FF82F211FED5FD16D0AFFD45" authorityName="Christ" authorityYear="1902" box="[358,497,698,724]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Polystichum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutidens">P. acutidens</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="DBD94D60FF82F211FE4DFD16D2E1FD44" authority="L. L. Xiang (1994: 265)" authorityName="L. L. Xiang" authorityPageNumber="265" authorityYear="1994" box="[510,959,698,725]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Polystichum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paradeltodon">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FE4DFD16D3ECFD45" box="[510,690,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">P. paradeltodon</emphasis>
L.L. 
<bibRefCitation id="78484B12FF82F211FD55FD17D2E1FD44" author="Xiang, L. - L." box="[742,959,698,725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" pagination="258 - 267" refId="ref3383" refString="Xiang, L. - L. (1994) A taxonomic study of the genus Polystichum Roth section Haplopolystichum Tagawa from Yunnan. Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica 32: 258 - 267." type="journal article" year="1994">Xiang (1994: 265)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and the new species being described here. 
<taxonomicName id="DBD94D60FF82F211FF3BFD73D0C3FD69" authorityName="Z. L. Liang &amp; Li Bing Zhang" authorityYear="2021" box="[136,413,734,760]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Polystichum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="menglaense">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FF3BFD73D0C3FD69" box="[136,413,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Polystichum menglaense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="DBD94D60FF82F211FD1FFD72D26DFD69" authorityName="Christ" authorityYear="1902" box="[684,819,734,760]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Polystichum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutidens">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FD1FFD72D26DFD69" box="[684,819,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">P. acutidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having rounded pinna apices (vs. acute pinna apices) and different from 
<taxonomicName id="DBD94D60FF82F211FEEEFCAED34EFC8D" authorityName="L. L. Xiang" authorityYear="1994" box="[349,528,770,796]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Polystichum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paradeltodon">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FEEEFCAED34EFC8D" box="[349,528,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">P. paradeltodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having oblong-lanceolate pinnae (vs. oblong pinnae) and partially fertile frond (vs. fully fertile frond). Both 
<taxonomicName id="DBD94D60FF82F211FE6BFC8BD3B1FCD1" authorityName="Z. L. Liang &amp; Li Bing Zhang" authorityYear="2021" box="[472,751,806,832]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Polystichum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="menglaense">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FE6BFC8BD3B1FCD1" box="[472,751,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Polystichum menglaense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DBD94D60FF82F211FC9AFC8AD283FCD1" authorityName="L. L. Xiang" authorityYear="1994" box="[809,989,806,832]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Polystichum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paradeltodon">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FC9AFC8AD283FCD1" box="[809,989,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">P. paradeltodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are calciphiles and very rare in Mengla, 
<collectingRegion id="DE1DF801FF82F211FF3BFCE6D1BFFCF4" box="[136,225,843,869]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="DBD94D60FF82F211FEFDFCE6D08BFCF5" authorityName="Christ" authorityYear="1902" box="[334,469,842,868]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Polystichum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutidens">
<emphasis id="2EADEAF1FF82F211FEFDFCE6D08BFCF5" box="[334,469,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">P. acutidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows in both acidic and basic soils and is more common.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
